column5: numbers are as follows so far 45 pike 1 bass 10 specks 1 rainbow 1 whitefish 62 perch 13 pickeral 9 lake trout for a total of 142 fish to date!  seeings as we are only 47 days into 2009  365/47=7.766  7.766x142=1120.7  this means that i'm on pace for my best season yet!  1120 fish for the year and gonna have to catch one with no tail to make that 0.7 i guess! lol  Matt!
Good luck with that Matt!  As for the one with no tail, bring in that bass nice and slow so one of those pike can take a bite and help you out there...
hahaha thanks! i was tryin to figure out how i was gonna pull that one off!
I'm at 23 lakers, 7 whities, 5 pike  Herring and perch -- only God could tell you that one.
i'll quit countin perch come march like every year, too bad no wallies for ya when you were on nipissing steve.
The only thing i've caught this year is the flu  lol.
A couple of pike , walleye , perch , the odd laker or two ...And no Whitefish yet !!!!!!!! that could change tomorrow
I've caught a cold and the chills.  Oh yeah...and hooked into a piece of ice that was floating down a trib.
I caught a whole whopping wait for this...       2 SMELT.......LOL & i was not even fishing for smelt.  ...lol  Hopefully that changes on sunday when i am fishing LPB on the ice.
85 bluegills 30 crappies 5 walleye 4 white bass an the flu to boot
i'm plannin on catchin some specks tomorrow numbers are no big deal but lookin for one over 5 pounds and as for the flu sorry to hear but dont pass it on! hahaha

Ok, what the heck, I'll add a tally. A total of 10 days spent on the ice this year, (a new personal low     ) was spent like this: 1 day on little lake for pike, 2 days on Nipissing, 2 days on Midland bay for herring, the rest on Simcoe. During these 10 days I caught 4 pike, 12 walleye, 6 whitefish, 19 lakers, with several perch and herring mixed in as well. Had 2 horrible days, one on Simcoe and the other on Midland Bay, but managed to avoid the skunk so far this year.
Sounds like a great year to me. I might try to keep track of just the bass i get, see how i do lol.  btw-Great math skills

hard to get a tally going for 2009 so far, but what I see in my pics is pretty close to  30-35 steelies, and 1 OOSer musky out of January and February so far, I have not gotten out nearly enough ion the last say 6-8 weeks    I guess that is not a bad average for that length of time although haven't had a 15-20 fish day on the river in a while
It never really occured to me to keep a count.
